<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF22703659BFF7282B3914A" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF22703659BFF7282B3914A" blockId="37.[151,1437,223,466]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
Four specimens, collected in southern 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF227036745FF4D83D990D5" box="[585,705,223,249]" name="Cameroon" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, field numbers MB 378–381, as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF22703613FFF4D801A9131" authority="(Bell et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Bell" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF22703613FFF4D845990D5" box="[1075,1345,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Hyperolius tuberculatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF22703605CFF4D81E29131" author="Bell" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" pagination="5223 - 5244" refId="ref28911" refString="Bell, R. C., Parra, J. L., Badjedjea, G., Barej, M. F., Blackburn, D. C., Burger, M., Channing, A., Dehling, J. M., Greenbaum, E., Gvozdik, V., Kielgast, J., Kusamba, C., Lotters, S., McLaughlin, P. J., Nagy, Z. T., Rodel, M. - O., Portik, D. M., Stuart, B. L., VanDerWal, J., Zassi-Boulou, A. G. &amp; Zamudio, K. R. (2017) Idiosyncratic responses to climate-driven forest fragmentation and marine incursions in reed frogs from Central Africa and the Gulf of Guinea Islands. Molecular Ecology, 26, 5223 - 5244. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mec. 14260" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bell 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF227036084FF7281B59131" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The uncorrected 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF2270364C3FE9680FE9131" box="[463,486,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 1.9–5.5% (
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF2270366EEFE9185249131" box="[994,1084,259,285]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Presently this species is only known from a single locality about 
<quantity id="4A3C62BDFFF227036729FEB58374916D" box="[549,620,295,322]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" unit="km" value="25.0">25 km</quantity>
inland from Campo, near Ekout Mintoum, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF2270361B7FEB58428916D" box="[1211,1328,295,321]" name="Cameroon" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF227036032FEB5848B916D" box="[1342,1427,295,321]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
) (
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF227036593FED980179149" box="[159,271,331,357]" degrees="2.3972" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" precision="5" value="2.3972">2.3972°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF227036417FED9808C914A" box="[283,404,331,358]" degrees="10.0452" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" precision="5" value="10.0452">10.0452°E</geoCoordinate>
) (
<figureCitation id="15FFD3DDFFF2270364A7FED9831B9149" box="[427,515,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,420,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-156@34.[151,1436,417,1940]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 8. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius nitidulus (A), H. mariae (B) and H. sp 1 (C). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538292/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). It is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF2270367FBFEDE82BC9149" box="[759,932,331,357]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF2270367FBFEDE82BC9149" box="[759,932,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">H. tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF2270365CBFEFD850891FD" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF2270365CBFEFD850891FD" blockId="37.[151,1437,223,466]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
The colour pattern and advertisement call are unknown. The voucher specimens could not be located during the preparation of this report. They are presumably still to be deposited in the Zoological Research Museum Alexander Koenig, along with other material of 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF22703673BFE2A83FC91FD" box="[567,740,439,465]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF22703673BFE2A83FC91FD" box="[567,740,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">H. tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same expedition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
